Equipment Trick												CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat																																																				PRETEXT:Base attack bonus +1.												PRETOTALAB:1											DESC:You understand how to use a certain item in combat.																																			STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:ABILITY|Special Ability|TYPE=EquipmentTrick	SOURCEPAGE:p.14				BENEFIT:You may use any equipment tricks relating to the item if you meet the appropriate trick requirements. If the item would normally be considered an improvised weapon, you may treat it as a normal weapon or an improvised weapon, whichever is more beneficial for you. You can gain the Equipment Trick feat multiple times. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a new type of equipment.
Extend the Bulwark											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Teamwork																																																																															DESC:You can bolster a trained ally's defenses by interposing your own armored body.																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.6				BENEFIT:If you are wearing medium or heavy armor and are adjacent to an ally who also has this feat, as a free action, you may give your ally a bonus to her AC equal to half the armor bonus provided by your armor. This bonus lasts for 1 round. During this round, you gain no bonus to your AC from your armor.
Quillbreaker Defense											CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat																																																				PRETEXT:Proficiency with armor spikes.																		PREWEAPONPROF:1,Spiked Armor	DESC:You know how to put armor spikes to defensive use by thrusting them into the path of an oncoming attack just in time.																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.6				BENEFIT:If you are wearing armor spikes, as an immediate action when you take damage from a nonmagical attack, you can give your armor spikes the broken condition to reduce the amount of damage you take by 5. If your armor spikes are already broken, they are destroyed instead. If you are wearing masterwork armor spikes, you instead reduce the damage by 10.
Shield Snag													CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat				PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Shield Bash,Two-Weapon Fighting					PREMULT:1,[PREPROFWITHSHIELD:3,TYPE.Buckler,TYPE.Light,TYPE.Heavy],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Shield Proficiency]													PRETEXT:Improved Shield Bash, Shield Proficiency, Two-Weapon Fighting, base attack bonus +6.	PRETOTALAB:6											DESC:You know how to navigate your shield around weapons and can use it to keep your balance.																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.6				BENEFIT:Any opponents hit by your shield bash are also targeted by a free disarm attempt that does not provoke an attack of opportunity. You cannot use this ability during the same round as a any other abilities that affect how your shield bash works. When using a shield, you gain a +4 on Strength checks to avoid being blown away by a strong wind and on Climb checks to catch yourself when falling.
Whip-Shot Deed												CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Grit				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Gunslinger ~ Pistol-Whip						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Gunslinger ~ Grit],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Amateur Gunslinger]													PRETEXT:Grit class feature or Amateur Gunslinger feat, pistol-whip deed.																	DESC:You can fire your weapon and strike with it at the same time.																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.22				BENEFIT:Whenever you use your pistol-whip deed, you can fire a single bullet from your firearm at the same time that you strike a foe with the butt of your firearm. You must spend a total of 2 grit points to use the pistol-whip deed in this way, and must still succeed at a ranged touch attack against the target of your pistol-whip deed to hit. You cannot use the scatter weapon quality of a firearm when you use this feat.

